resource.name: SCALE Sensor Data (Beta - For Demonstration Purposes Only)
resource.description: This dataset shared the data collected by sensors deployed in Rockville using the Safe Community Awareness and Alerting (SCALE) Network devices developed by the County's Innovation Office. This dataset is currently in beta and should be used only for demonstration purposes at this time.
columns_description: This field identifies the device containing the sensors. It is important not to mix data from different devices. Examples of this field include "scale-2", "scale-5", etc.
Light value in arbitrary units that range from 0 to 1023; this field is empty if device doesn't have a light sensor.
Motion detected, True or False; this field is empty if device doesn't have a motion sensor.
Carbon monoxide reading in arbitrary units that range from 0 to 1023; this field is empty if device doesn't have a CO sensor.
If populated, this is the time when the measurement was taken; time format is in Eastern Standard Time (converted from ISO 8601 UTC).

If the Time of Measurement (TIME_RAW) field is empty, this is the time when the measurement was taken; if Time of Measurement (TIME_RAW) has a value, this is the time when the measurement was received by the communications system; time format is ISO 8601 UTC.
Temperature in degrees Fahrenheit; this field is empty if device doesn't have a temperature sensor.
Relative humidity in percent that ranges from 0 to 100; this field is empty if device doesn't have a humidity sensor.
